  footnotes: []
english:
  title: To Reverend Hye
  author: Byeon Gyeryang
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The mountain path stretches far, half-hidden in clouds above.
    This journey offers escape from the clamor of dusty existence.
    A hundred years of life—a wanderer lost upon the road,
    While the monk behind closed doors sits wrapped in mist and rosy light.

    By the clear stream I bundle firewood with an old villager,
    In the autumn forest I pluck fruit with the shivering monkeys.
    I enter the meditation hall hoping to ask about the Lankavatara Sutra,
    But the master only closes his eyes, bows his head—and speaks not a word.
  footnotes:
    - The Lankavatara Sutra (Lenga-jing in Chinese, 능가경 in Korean) is a key Buddhist text emphasizing sudden enlightenment and the primacy of mind-consciousness. The poet's unanswered question suggests that ultimate truth transcends verbal teaching.
